text: 11-1 King Street, north side, and 8-2, east side, east from Congress Street (which will become the west side of the future Sixth Avenue Extension at this point). NOS. 13-7, at the left, and 8 and 6, the three-story houses on the right, will be demolished when the new subway and Sixth Avenue Extension (q.v.) are put through, beginning the year after. No. 9-5, adjoining the N.E. corner of Congress Street, is the abandoned building of the Alexander Presbyterian Church. 1926.
